article.headline: CS Northridge 80, Denver 53
article.story: LOS ANGELES -- Tremaine Townsend scored 14 points as Cal State Northridge ended a six-game losing streak with a 80-53 victory over Denver on Tuesday. Willie Galick scored 12 of his 14 points in the second half and grabbed 10 rebounds for Northridge (2-6). The Matadors dominated from the start, opening with a 12-2 run and building a 35-22 halftime lead. Denver (1-6) did not get closer than six points the rest of the way. Deon Tresvant scored 13 points, and Josh Jenkins added 13 points and nine assists. Rob Lewis scored a season-best 18 points for Denver, which lost its 36th consecutive road game -- the second longest active streak in Division I, dating to March 5, 2006. Nate Rohnert added 12 points, and Brian Stafford scored 10 points for Denver.
